b'       INDIAN INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY MADRAS  Academic Section      Circular No. 26C/JM2016/B2/2016;&n;bsp; &nbs;p;&nbsp;&nbs;p;Dated 21.04.2016      Sub: Production of Identity Cards during Quizzes and Examinations  Reg.      End Semester examination  for the B.Tech./Dual Degree/M.Tech./MBA/M.Sc. /M.A. / MS and Ph.D students/scholars commences on  Thursday  the  28 th  April 2016   All students should carry with them their Identity Cards to the Quizzes/ Examinations. They should produce their identity card to the Invigilator. If, for any reason, they are not able to produce the Identity Cards at the time of examination, the Head of the Department/Invigilator may permit them to write the examination, with the condition that they should produce the Identity Card to the Head of the Department/ Invigilator(s) within one hour after the closure of the examination. In case some students do not possess or have lost their Identity Cards, they are required to meet the Librarian immediately, and get new identity card made, against the payment of Rs.500/. In the case of any correction to be made, fresh card will be issued on payment of Rs.250/.  Sd/ Deputy Registrar (Courses)  To All students  thro students@list.iitm.ac.in  Copy to : 1. All Heads of Departments  thro email 2. The Dean, Students  thro email 3. The Librarian, Central Library  thro email 4. All faculty thro faculty@list.iitm.ac.in    '

